      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Three things to know:\n\n\n\tAmong Igor Stravinsky’s most cinematic scores, The Firebird was heard in movie theatres around the world in Disney’s Fantasia 2000.\n\tInspired by jazz, blues, and ragtime, George Gershwin’s concerto for solo piano and orchestra will immediately transport you to 1920s New York.\n\tOur musicians will be joined by members of the NACO Mentorship Program, who represent some of today’s brightest early-career artists.\n\n\nComposed two years before Igor Stravinsky caused riots in Paris with The Rite of Spring, his ballet The Firebird hypnotized the..."
      }
    ],
